
[1]gratuitous

   GRATU'ITOUS, a. [L. gratuitus, from gratus.]

   1. Free; voluntary; not required by justice; granted without claim or
   merit.

   We mistake the gratuitous blessings of heaven for the fruits of our own
   industry.

   2. Asserted or taken without proof; as a gratuitous argument or
   affirmation.
